President Joe Biden on Instagram: “Welcome to the White House, President Yoon and Mrs. Kim.”

Women's body, women's choice. The end.

It's time for public school teachers to get a raise.

Thank you, President @petrogustavo , for your commitment to addressing climate change and promoting democratic values across the Americas. When Colombia and the United States stand together, there's nothing we can't accomplish.

MAGA Congressional Republicans’ budget pushes for tax giveaways that overwhelmingly benefit the wealthiest Americans and biggest corporations.

It was our honor to stand alongside President Yoon Suk Yeol and Mrs. Kim at the Korean War Memorial.

Today, on my orders, the United States military conducted an operation to extract U.S. Government personnel from Khartoum in response to the situation in Sudan. I am grateful for the commitment of our Embassy staff and the skill of our service members who brought them to safety.

Teachers have champions in this White House. Jill is the first to teach full time as First Lady, grading papers here at the White House.Like she reminds me: teaching is not just what you do – it’s who you are

Things like the Dependent Care Flex Savings also haven't been indexed for inflation. It's been $5,000 since 1986 and the cost of childcare has more than doubled. All money spent on childcare should be tax free.

After a tragic shooting in Nashville, Reps. Justin Jones, Justin Pearson, and Gloria Johnson stood up against gun violence. Jones and Pearson were silenced and expelled by Republican legislators. Now, they're back at work, and today we met to discuss their crucial efforts.

Every community has a right to clean air and water. And after my Executive Order on environmental justice, we're one step closer.

I’m not waiting to tackle the climate crisis. The signs are unmistakable. The science is undeniable. And the cost of inaction keeps mounting.

No billionaire should pay less in taxes than a school teacher or a firefighter.

We ask so much of our nation’s teachers – and each and every time, you say yes. Not to mention, the impact you have on your students is profound. I’ll always have your back.
